<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-74-0766 </DOCNO><TEXT>A report from the Ministry's Working Committee on Greenlands's energypolicy had recommended that, in the future, the contry's energy productionshould be based on coal and, primarily, water power. This was in orderthat Greenland could be independent of oil import and thus cut down onenergy expenses. The economical aspects of this policy are discussed,especially in relation to the power supply in specific urban areas. Thepossibility of optimally exploiting domestic energy resources are consideredin detail. (AB).</TEXT></DOC>